														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1384100">
									

<p>Satisfyingly creepy idea&#8212; but too purple for an upvote, as is.</p>
<p>I mean, &quot;She didn’t tell any of them of the mind-blowing spikes that had lodged themselves in her chest, that sparked her fire and drove her insane.&quot; That line could be from a fanfic. Mind-blowing spikes? That blow her mind and her&#8230; chest?</p>
<p>Plus, the squelching and the rivulets and the spray and streams and overall bloody juiciness kept the descriptions from being as sharp (and as unsettling) as they could have been. Also &quot;nubile&quot; should be retired from internet use (along with &quot;lithe&quot;, possibly), and &quot;searched online&quot; gives me the image of an intense Google montage and should go. There's just excess in all the wrong places.</p>
<p>I suggest taking a razor to it&#8230; in the strictly editorial sense.</p>

							</div>

								
					
