														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1384606">
									

<p>Of course it doesn't, what I was saying was that I merely was trying out a different style of writing. And the laboriousness of Guts is well&#8230; I'd say that's a very subjective thing. On one hand, you're right, he does use shorter sentences, on the other hand, I find that his description is filled with adjectives. Anyway, the point is that what I was trying to do was to assault readers with this description, the number of modifiers was meant to disturb and put readers off-guard, cause them unease. Maybe I over-did it, but in the context of this story, I don't think that was a mistake per se, at most, not as well done as I had hoped it would be.</p>
<p>I do understand what you're saying though, I used to suffer from written diarrhea, quite badly. This story though, was more a controlled stream (eugh, pardon the image) rather than me just plonking all the adjectives I knew into the line.</p>

							</div>

								
					
